  <source>McMaster University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To determine whether treatment and further investigation can be safely withheld in patients
      who present with suspected recurrent deep vein thrombosis (DVT) and have either a (i)
      negative D-Dimer or (ii) a positive D-Dimer with normal serial compression ultrasound.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
